<br>
The thing that makes it worse is that every computer with a word processor probably has a spell-checker. If you are writing a story or a script then it's not that hard to do the basic checks. When I see a writer that hasn't done that, especially on the internet, I automatically begin to assume that this writer is some kid for whom writing is just a month-long phase and who doesn't care enough about the craft to make sure it's done properly. Most of the times I skip those stories, because if he doesn't care enough, why should I?<br>
<br>
Compare it to the art section on any messageboard. The people who you can tell are serious are the ones who make sure the lines are straight, that they didn't use lined paper, who planned their drawings before they drew. If that person does not draw perfect anatomy, I can tell he is willing to put in the time it takes to learn. <br>
<br>
If a writer does not take the time to work on his grammar, what reason do I have for thinking that he/she would take the time to work out any issues with plotting that he/she might have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utarotgirl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarotGirl</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/25/02 9:47:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My two cents</span><hr size=1> Anything with poor grammer becomes a chore to read. If you think your stuff is so good that you don't need to fix it or that if people don't want to wade through your grammer mistakes then you yourself aren't taking the work seriously and that's doing a great injustice to writing. If you are going to break a rule (mine is comma splicing because it's the style I use.. think poetry..) then you had better have a reason for it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=803.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=803.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=803.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.c